From 66e844303c0213e6a06d081fd24589286f1c38f2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Joey Riches <josephriches@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2026 15:43:58 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 1/4] sax: Use LUTs for character classification

Previously, the parser consisted of a big ol' while loop that was
iterated on byte by byte, where each byte had to be matched against several
if/switch cases.

By introducing LUTs, we can continually iterate over chucks until we do
find a special character, then handle it explicitly, instead of
checking byte by byte.

In practice, this provided a 1.44x speedup parsing and building a
real-world ~70MiB XML file.

A python script is also provided for LUT generation and validation.

This will help enable more optimization oppotunities such as SWAR/SIMD
whilst we are processing CDATA for example.
